ury, with the structural collapse of the Roman Empire in the west, Western Europe had fallen into the so-called Dark Ages. With the power of Rome removed, the Catholic Church stepped in to fill the void. Its political rise, alongside that of the Germanic kingdoms, led to dramatic changes in law, politics, power, and culture. Against the backdrop of that upheaval, the family became a vitally important area of focus for cultural struggles related to morality, law, and tradition. This book explores those battles in order to demonstrate, through the family, the intersections between Roman and Christian legal culture, thought, and political power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aFamilieszEurope, WesternxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aMarriage customs and rites, MedievalzEurope, Western. 0aMarriage lawzEurope, WesternyTo 1500. 0aMarriagezEurope, WesternxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aParenthoodzEurope, WesternxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAntiquity. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aFamily, Christianity, Early Medieval West, Law, Late Antiquity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048529612zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048529612423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048529612/original  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Packag